Krasnoarmeysky_District,_Primorsky_Krai
dateJanuary 2011Krasnoarmeysky District () is an administrative( and municipal( district (raion) of Krai, Russia; one of the twenty-two in the krai. It is located in the central portion of the krai and borders with District in the northwest and north, District in the east, the territory of the town of Dalnegorsk in the south, and with District in the southwest and west. The area of the district is .( Its center is the rural locality (a selo) of Novopokrovka. Districts population: 20,172 (2010 est.);(  Population of Novopokrovka accounts for 19.4% of the districts population.(The climate conditions of the Krasnoarmeysky District sharply differ from those on the coast. Sikhote-Alin mountain range is a natural barrier which blocks the penetration of the monsoonal winds from the south and the east, forming a specific microclimate of the district. Frosts of  are very frequent in winter, while in summer the heat exceeds . The mean annual temperature is  (compare with  in the south of the krai). Despite the climate conditions, however, the population of the district grows apples, plums, cherries, and watermelons.Tungsten and timber, fur and gold are produced in the district. The Primorsky Ore Mining and Processing Enterprise operates in the area.Nature Reserve is in the eastern part of the district. The major rivers of the district are the Bolshaya Ussurka and Armu.The Sikhote-Alin newspaper is published on the districts territory.ReferencesSources**rajon (Territorio del Litorale)jrs (Tengermellk) ( )  
