Goldsworthy
Goldsworthy is a Cornish surname, and place name, from the language gol-erewy, meaning field of feast. It can can refer to:* Goldsworthy (born 1969), British historian* Goldsworthy (born 1956), British artist* Goldsworthy (born 1974), Australian pianist and writer, daughter of Peter Goldsworthy* Goldsworthy (born 1944), Canadian ice hockey player* Goldsworthy (c.1705-1774), 18th century English Consul at Leghorn and later Cadiz* Goldsworthy, a fictional character in Degrassi* E. Goldsworthy (born 1914), American Air Force lieutenant general * Goldsworthy (born 1978), British politician* Goldsworthy (born 1956), Australian anglican bishop* Goldsworthy (1953), Australian writer* Goldsworthy (born 1951), Australian author, father of Anna Goldsworthy* Goldsworthy (1839&ndash;1900), President of Nevis; Governor of Saint Lucia; Governor of the British Honduras; and Governor of the Falkland Islands* Goldsworthy (1855&ndash;1889), Wales international rugby player* Brandt Goldsworthy, the pioneer of pultrusion* Lowes Dickinson(1863&ndash;1932), Historian and political activist;Places named Goldsworthy* Western Australia, a former mining town in the Shire of East Pilbara* railway, an iron ore railway line operated by BHP Billiton* Goldsworthy, Gwennap, Cornwall* Goldsworthy, Crowan, CornwallSee also*Source*White, G. Pawley, A Handbook of Cornish Surnames.(Penrose mentioned by name)de:Goldsworthyko:
